## 2. ❌ Issues Found

### 🔴 Critical Bugs

#### BUG-1 — MeetingsPage shows cancelled bookings in "Upcoming" tab
**File:** [AppContext.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx) L155, [MeetingsPage.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/MeetingsPage.tsx) L13-22

`refreshMeetings()` fetches both `/api/booking/upcoming` and `/api/booking/past` and merges them into one flat array. Then [MeetingsPage](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/MeetingsPage.tsx#6-113) re-splits them client-side by date only — it **ignores `status`**. So a cancelled meeting with a future date will appear in the "Upcoming" tab.

The backend `/api/booking/upcoming` already filters `status: "scheduled"` correctly, but the client discards that distinction by merging both arrays.

```
❌ meetings = [...upcoming, ...past]  // status info lost
❌ MeetingsPage splits by date only — cancelled meetings with future dates show in Upcoming
```

#### BUG-2 — Slug not sent on Edit; backend silently passes `undefined` slug
**File:** [AppContext.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx) L185, [eventType.controller.js](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/controllers/eventType.controller.js) L97

When editing an event type, the frontend sends `{ title, duration }` but NOT `slug`. The backend update handler computes `slug` from `title` — but only if `title` is provided. When a user edits only duration (no title change), `slug` becomes `undefined` and the Prisma [update](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#184-188) sets `slug: undefined`, which Prisma ignores — this is safe but inconsistent. However if a user changes the title, the slug auto-regenerates silently without showing the new slug to the user.

#### BUG-3 — [cancelBooking](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/controllers/booking.controller.js#71-92) endpoint uses DELETE but backend does soft-delete only
**File:** [booking.route.js](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/routes/booking.route.js) L18, [booking.controller.js](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/controllers/booking.controller.js) L82-85

The route is `router.delete("/:id", ...)` but the handler does `prisma.booking.update({ data: { status: "cancelled" } })`. This is a semantic mismatch — a `DELETE` HTTP method should delete the resource. Additionally, `AppContext.cancelMeeting` calls `api.delete()` — however the [Booking](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/BookingPage.tsx#18-249) DELETE route is protected by [defaultUserOrAuth](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/middleware/auth.middleware.js#35-46), while `POST /api/booking` (create) has **no auth guard at all**, meaning anyone can book on someone else's event type.

#### BUG-4 — `new Date(date)` timezone offset bug in [getSlots](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#239-245) and [MeetingsPage](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/MeetingsPage.tsx#6-113)
**File:** [booking.controller.js](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/controllers/booking.controller.js) L126, [MeetingsPage.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/MeetingsPage.tsx) L15

```js
const day = new Date(date).getDay();  // date = "2025-04-01" (ISO string)
```
`new Date("2025-04-01")` is parsed as **UTC midnight**, so in negative UTC-offset timezones (e.g. `America/New_York`), `.getDay()` returns the **previous day** (March 31 = Sunday instead of Tuesday April 1). This breaks slot availability — the wrong day's availability is queried.

Same issue in [MeetingsPage.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/MeetingsPage.tsx) L15: `new Date(meeting.date)` shifts one day back in UTC- timezones.

---

### 🟡 Non-Critical Issues

#### ISSUE-5 — `timezone` is stored only in React state, never sent to backend
**File:** [AppContext.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx) L105, [availability.controller.js](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/controllers/availability.controller.js)

The selected timezone is never persisted. If the user refreshes, the timezone resets to `'America/New_York'`. More importantly, the backend generates slots in plain `HH:MM` strings with no timezone conversion — all times are treated as whatever timezone the server runs in.

#### ISSUE-6 — Slug prefix in modal shows `schedulr.com/` (hardcoded), but actual URL is `localhost:5173/book/`
**File:** [EventFormModal.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/components/EventFormModal.tsx) L95

This is a cosmetic mismatch that will confuse users in production.

#### ISSUE-7 — [handleBookingSubmit](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/BookingPage.tsx#109-137) in [BookingPage](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/BookingPage.tsx#18-249) uses `alert()` on error
**File:** [BookingPage.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/BookingPage.tsx) L134

The [Dashboard.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/Dashboard.tsx) and [MeetingsPage.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/MeetingsPage.tsx) use `toast.success/error` (Sonner). [BookingPage.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/BookingPage.tsx) uses `alert()` — inconsistent UX.

#### ISSUE-8 — [Availability](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#19-28) missing `onDelete: Cascade` for `eventTypeId` FK
**File:** [schema.prisma](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/prisma/schema.prisma) L38

```diff
- eventType    EventType @relation(fields: [eventTypeId], references: [id])
+ eventType    EventType @relation(fields: [eventTypeId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
```
Same for [Booking](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/BookingPage.tsx#18-249). If an [EventType](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#6-13) is deleted, Prisma cascades from [User](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/controllers/auth.controller.js#34-37) → [EventType](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#6-13) but not from [EventType](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#6-13) → [Availability](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#19-28) / [Booking](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/BookingPage.tsx#18-249), which will throw a FK constraint error at runtime.

> ⚠️ **This will cause a 500 error when deleting an event type that has bookings.**

#### ISSUE-9 — [availability.route.js](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/routes/availability.route.js) has a dead `PUT /:id` route
**File:** [availability.route.js](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/routes/availability.route.js) L8

`router.put("/:id", defaultUserOrAuth, setAvailability)` — the [setAvailability](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/controllers/availability.controller.js#14-64) handler switches on `Array.isArray(slots) && eventTypeId` from `req.body`, not from `req.params.id`. The `:id` param is never read. This route is dead code.

#### ISSUE-10 — [MeetingsPage](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/MeetingsPage.tsx#6-113) splits meetings client-side but backend already splits them
`AppContext.refreshMeetings` hits both `/upcoming` and `/past` and merges. The meeting tab then re-splits by date. This is redundant work and introduces the BUG-1 desync.

