## 4. 🔧 Fix Suggestions

### Fix BUG-1 — Preserve status in meetings; filter correctly in MeetingsPage

**[AppContext.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx)** — Add `status` to [Meeting](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#29-39) interface and map it:
```ts
// In Meeting interface
status: 'scheduled' | 'cancelled';

// In refreshMeetings mapping
status: String(item.status) as 'scheduled' | 'cancelled',
```

**[MeetingsPage.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/pages/MeetingsPage.tsx)** — Filter cancelled out of upcoming:
```ts
const upcoming = meetings.filter(m => {
  const d = new Date(m.date + 'T00:00:00'); // Fix BUG-4 too
  d.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
  return d >= today && m.status === 'scheduled';  // ← add status check
});
```

---

### Fix BUG-4 — UTC date parsing offset

In **[booking.controller.js](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/src/controllers/booking.controller.js) L126**, append time to force local parsing:
```js
// ❌ Wrong — parsed as UTC midnight, shifts day in UTC- timezones
const day = new Date(date).getDay();

// ✅ Correct — force local date parsing
const day = new Date(date + 'T00:00:00').getDay();
```

Apply same fix everywhere `new Date(dateString)` is used with a `YYYY-MM-DD` string.

---

### Fix ISSUE-8 — Add cascade deletes to schema

```prisma
model Availability {
  // ...
  eventType   EventType @relation(fields: [eventTypeId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
}

model Booking {
  // ...
  eventType   EventType @relation(fields: [eventTypeId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
}
```
Then run: `npx prisma migrate dev --name add_cascade_deletes`

---

### Fix ISSUE-6 — Dynamic slug prefix in modal

**[EventFormModal.tsx](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/components/EventFormModal.tsx) L95:**
```tsx
// ❌ Hardcoded
<span className="...">schedulr.com/</span>

// ✅ Use actual origin + path
<span className="...">{window.location.origin}/book/</span>
```

---

### Fix ISSUE-5 — Persist timezone in DB

Add to [schema.prisma](file:///e:/SCALER/BACKEND/prisma/schema.prisma):
```prisma
model User {
  // existing fields...
  timezone  String @default("UTC")
}
```
Then save the timezone on the [updateAvailability](file:///e:/SCALER/FRONTEND/src/app/context/AppContext.tsx#194-218) call and read it back on `/api/me`.

---

### Fix BUG-3 — Add auth guard to `POST /api/booking`
This endpoint should at minimum be rate-limited. If you want to keep it public (for invitees without accounts), add express-rate-limit:
```js
// booking.route.js
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
const bookingLimiter = rateLimit({ windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, max: 20 });
router.post('/', bookingLimiter, createBooking);
```

---

## 5. 🚀 Final Verdict

### **NO — Not submission-ready yet (7/10)**

The core flows work and the UI is polished. However, **2 critical bugs** block correctness:

| # | Blocker | Severity |
|---|---------|----------|
| BUG-1 | Cancelled meetings appear in Upcoming tab | 🔴 |
| BUG-3/8 | Deleting an event type with bookings crashes with FK error | 🔴 |
| BUG-4 | Wrong day-of-week in UTC-offset timezones breaks slot availability | 🔴 |

Fix those 3 bugs (estimated ~30 min of work), and the project becomes **submission-ready**. The architecture, API design, and UI quality are genuinely strong.

**Positive highlights:**
- Clean MVC backend with proper auth middleware
- Booking double-prevention at DB level
- Calendly-accurate UI with correct color system
- TanStack Query integration for reactive event types
- Prisma transactions for atomic event-type creation with availability seeding
